EAST LONDON - As the African National Congress (ACN) formally celebrated its 106th anniversary on Monday, the party's top six proved you can indeed have your cake and eat it too.  The governing party's celebration kicked off in East London where the top 6 office bearers cut a cake decorated with the party's colours. WATCH: Bullish ANC in KZN Newly-elected president, Cyril Ramaphosa arrived from Durban and addressed the gathering. He'll deliver the party's annual January 8th Statement on Saturday. eNCA